# Metadata for THEODICY-1
**Original location:** `More My Documents/CCWin9/CHANTILL/THEODICY`
**Date:** April 14, 1992

**Note:** Date recovered from document internal dating.

**Type:** academic

**Category:** Philosophy of Religion / Medieval Philosophy / Theology
**Abstract:** Examines the relationship between theodicy (natural theology) and metaphysics, paralleling the relationship between philosophy of religion and religion itself. Traces the historical transformation of Christian theology from practical, intra-communitary reflection on Scripture to an academic discipline focused on theoretical knowledge, culminating in the Summae Theologicae. Argues that Peter Lombard's systematization began the shift from practical to theoretical theology.
**AI Recommendation:** HIGH - Central to understanding Monasterio's critique of the scientization of theology; important analysis of the shift from practical to theoretical knowledge in Western thought.
**Original format:** No extension (likely WordPerfect)

